This is JAFFA version 1.06

Installation under linux x86_64 (other systems not supported)
-------------------------------------------------------------
1. Run:
   ./install_linux64.sh

   Check that all paths are filled in the file tools.groovy. Note that you will need to install 
   R yourself (or have it preinstalled on your system).

2. Download the supporting reference files into this directory:
   wget --no-check-certificate https://googledrive.com/host/0B1FwZagazjpcQU9IaURTVzd6Ym8/JAFFA_REFERENCE_FILES_GENCODE19.tar.gz
   tar -zxvf JAFFA_REFERENCE_FILES_GENCODE19.tar.gz

3. Sym. link or copy the human reference genome into this directory

Running
-------

If bpipe is installed centrally on your system you can run the pipeline like so:
bpipe run [option] < JAFFA_assembly.groovy | hybrid | direct > input files

If bpipe was installed into tools/bin you will need to run the pipeline like so:
<path to JAFFA source>/tools/bin/bpipe run [option] < JAFFA_assembly.groovy | hybrid | direct > input files

Please visit https://code.google.com/p/jaffa-project/ for more detailed running instructions.
Questions should be directed to the google group linked to on this page.

Written and maintained by Nadia Davidson, Murdoch Childrens Research Institute, Parkville, Australia.
